                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <seg type="para">This fragment is made of one loose leaf and a bifolium containing some
                                letters of <title>Meletius I Pegas</title> (1549-1601), Greek Patriarch of Alexandria between 1590 and 1601.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">The leaves have been incorrectly foliated, and text runs from ff. 2r-3v to 1r-1v.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Matteo Di Franco</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <!--<locus from="2r" to="1v">ff. 2r-1v</locus>-->
                            <author key="person_v47607458">Meletios I, Patriarch of Alexandria, approximately 1551-1601</author>
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Letters 4, line 29 - 7, line 15 (ed. Methodios 1970-1975)</title>
                            <incipit defective="true">
                        <locus from="2r" to="2r">f. 2r</locus>
                                καὶ ἡμετέρου υἱοῦ, μεθ’ οὗ εἰ βούλεται ἡ σὴ αὐθεντία γραψάτω πρὸς ἡμᾶς 
                                περὶ ὧν ἀνωτέρω ἐδηλώσαμεν</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="1v" to="1v">f. 1v</locus>
                                ἄλλως ἢ ὡς ἐβουλόμεθα ὠκονόμηται· τῇ θεία μὲν χάριτι, ἔχειν τε χρεὼν χάριν 
                                καὶ ὁμολογεῖν</explicit>
                            <note>TLG 9058.001</note>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>

